      {
        "id": 7552,
        "name": "Omid Bakhshandeh",
        "username": "omidb",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/omidb/{size}/925_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-07-08T18:54:38.633Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I think just extending Serializable would be a great start.</p>\n<p>I understand that FDB doesn\u2019t want to get into direct incorporation with analytical tools but for a company to decide if they want to use FDB or not it\u2019s important to know that it\u2019s at least not very hard to do those works themselves.</p>\n<p>It would be cool side repo if FDB could have a test repo that contains simple examples of how to incorporate the database with the heavily used analytical frameworks like Spark and Flink. It could help everyone to understand what is needed to include in the main project bindings like the level of serializability, async frameworks, etc.</p>",
        "post_number": 3,
        "post_type": 1,
